      Storytelling
      and Narrative: "The Last of Us" is often praised for its strong narrative.
      It focuses on the characters of Joel and Ellie and their development throughout
      a post-apocalyptic journey, delivering an emotionally impactful story that
      has resonated with many players.


      Aesthetics and Visuals: "BioShock
      Infinite" stands out for its unique aesthetic and art direction. The floating
      city of Columbia is rich in detail and style, combining elements of historical
      architecture with fantastical designs, which helps to build a memorable game
      world.


      User Interface and Usability: "Portal 2" features a highly intuitive
      and minimalist user interface that is seamlessly integrated into the game environment.
      The UI provides clear feedback without overwhelming the player, thus maintaining
      immersion and guiding the player through increasingly complex puzzles.


